  "title": "Adding options.templates.allItems to refinementList widget (similar to the hits widget)",
  "body": "I'm trying to gain more control over the refinementList widget template and how it is rendered.  In this case I'm specifically trying to create a 3 column layout with results alphabetized down column 1, then down column 2, and finally down column 3.  I'm unable to achieve this with the the way the current template renders HTML and custom CSS.  \n\nI need to write my own custom template to handle it but I need to be able to iterate over the entire collection of refinements as opposed to just having access to them one at a time (like the options.templates.item property currently provides).\n\nHere's what I'd like to see (similar to what you implemented to in the hits widget)\n\n``` javascript\ninstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\n    templates:{\n        allItems: myRenderingFunction\n    }\n});\n\nmyRenderinfFunction = function(refinements){\n //here I can loop through all refinements and build the HTML however I need\n}\n```\n\nPerhaps I'm missing an already easy way to do this - I'm not sure.  Any thoughts?\n",
